08/08/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH House of Representatives gave its support to the draft security law Thursday (7 August), but asked the government and the presidency to include some adjustments before final approval.
The document, called the Security Policy of Bosnia and Herzegovina, assesses border risks and sets up concrete policy targets.The lower house insisted on more detailed reform measures to be included in the draft.
The revised version should be passed back to the parliament in 90 days.
At a plenary session on Thursday, meanwhile, the House of Representatives adopted the telecommunications law.
The act regulates the statute of the Telecommunications Regulatory Agency, telecom services and supply of related equipment.
The vote followed an emergency procedure recommended by the Office of the High Representative.
(BNTV1, SRNA - 07/08/03)
